===Nicknames===
[[File:Uzbekistan vs Bahrain 2009.jpg|thumb|right|280px|Uzbekistan vs. Bahrain at Pakhtakor Central Stadium in 2009]]
The Uzbekistan national team has received several nicknames by supporters and media. The most common one used is "The White Wolves" ({{langx|uz|Oq bo{{okina}}rilar|italic=yes}}  ''/ {{lang|uz-cyrl|Оқ бўрилар}}''),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-asian-cup/latest/news/cuper-ready-to-power-uzbekistan|title=Cuper ready to power Uzbekistan|work=AFC|access-date=7 January 2019|archive-date=30 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181130030241/http://www.the-afc.com/competitions/afc-asian-cup/latest/news/cuper-ready-to-power-uzbekistan|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/2018-fifa-world-cup-qualifiers-uzbekistan-1-0-qatar-white-wolves-/8f7bb0ethytk12gxpmhnmzvdv|title=2018 FIFA World Cup Qualifiers: Uzbekistan 1-0 Qatar - White Wolves pile further misery on the Maroons|work=Goal.com|access-date=7 January 2019|archive-date=30 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181130073019/https://www.goal.com/en-us/news/2018-fifa-world-cup-qualifiers-uzbekistan-1-0-qatar-white-wolves-/8f7bb0ethytk12gxpmhnmzvdv|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://championat.asia/ru/uzb/news/uzbekistan-football-federation-president-mirabror-usmanov-met-with-junior-white-wolves|title=Uzbekistan Football Federation President Mirabror Usmanov Met With Junior White Wolves|work=Championat.asia|access-date=7 January 2019|archive-date=30 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181130030246/https://championat.asia/ru/uzb/news/uzbekistan-football-federation-president-mirabror-usmanov-met-with-junior-white-wolves|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jfrWCQAAQBAJ&q=white+wolves+uzbekistan&pg=PA199|title=James Minahan. The Complete Guide to National Symbols and Emblems|isbn=9780313344978|access-date=7 January 2019|last1=Minahan|first1=James B.|date=23 December 2009|publisher=Abc-Clio|archive-date=20 September 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230920074239/https://books.google.com/books?id=jfrWCQAAQBAJ&q=white+wolves+uzbekistan&pg=PA199|url-status=live}}</ref> while also being called "Asian Italy"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sports.ru/tribuna/blogs/new_course/2297826.html|title=Кубок Азии – 2019. Группа F. Сборная Узбекистана. Белые волки Турана|work=sports.ru|date=30 December 2018|access-date=7 January 2019|archive-date=7 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190107181222/https://www.sports.ru/tribuna/blogs/new_course/2297826.html|url-status=live}}</ref> ({{langx|uz|Osiyo Italiyasi|links=no|italic=yes}} ''/ {{lang|uz-cyrl|Осиё Италияси}}'') due to the similarity of colors (white and blue) of [[Italy national football team|Italy]] and Uzbekistan, as well as similar tactics (defensive football) of these teams.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sports.ru/tribuna/blogs/new_course/2297826.html|title=Кубок Азии – 2019. Группа F. Сборная Узбекистана. Белые волки Турана|work=sports.ru|date=30 December 2018|access-date=7 January 2019|archive-date=7 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190107181222/https://www.sports.ru/tribuna/blogs/new_course/2297826.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

Uzbekistan is also called the "[[Huma bird]]s" ({{langx|uz|Humo qushlari|links=no|italic=yes}} ''/ {{lang|uz-cyrl|Ҳумо қушлари}}''); the mythical Huma bird is the national bird of Uzbekistan, and is depicted on the [[Emblem of Uzbekistan|state emblem of Uzbekistan]]. The Huma bird is depicted on the emblem of the [[National Olympic Committee of the Republic of Uzbekistan]].{{Citation needed|date=March 2025}} Another nickname is the "Turanians"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sports.ru/tribuna/blogs/new_course/2297826.html|title=Кубок Азии – 2019. Группа F. Сборная Узбекистана. Белые волки Турана|work=sports.ru|date=30 December 2018|access-date=7 January 2019|archive-date=7 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190107181222/https://www.sports.ru/tribuna/blogs/new_course/2297826.html|url-status=live}}</ref> ({{langx|uz|Turonliklar|links=no|italic=yes}} ''/ {{lang|uz-cyrl|Туронликлар}}''), as Uzbekistan is located in the center of the ancient region of [[Turan]].<ref>''Turon'' — [[National Encyclopedia of Uzbekistan]], 2000–2005</ref><ref>''Бартольд В. В.'' Работы по истории и филологии тюркских и монгольских народов / В. В. Бартольд; — Перепеч. с изд. 1968 г. — М. — {{ISBN|9785020183391}} (в пер.)</ref>

===Rivalries===
[[File:TUR-UZB 20190113 Asian Cup 1.jpg|thumb|right|280px|Uzbekistani fans at the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup|2019 Asian Cup in UAE]]]]
Uzbekistan's main rivals are [[China national football team|China]] and [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]]. [[Iran national football team|Iran]] also became a recent fierce rival since the Persians joined the [[Central Asian Football Federation]] in 2015. Both teams played also in 2014, 2018, 2022 and 2026 World Cup qualifiers.{{Citation needed|date=June 2025}}

