==Home stadium==
[[File:Bunyodkor stadium2.jpg|thumb|right|250px|[[Milliy Stadium]]]]
[[File:Pakhtakor Markaziy Stadium.jpg|thumb|left|250px|[[Pakhtakor Central Stadium]]]]
From its formation in 1992 until the end of 2012, the main home stadium of the Uzbekistan national football team was the [[Pakhtakor Central Stadium]] in [[Tashkent]], built and opened in 1956. This stadium is also the venue for [[Pakhtakor Tashkent FK|Pakhtakor Football Club]]. During the Soviet Union, this stadium was home for the Uzbekistan SSR national team. It was reconstructed in 1996, 2008 and 2012 and currently holds 35,000 spectators, previously at 55,000 spectators. The team also uses [[Milliy Stadium]] (formerly known as Bunyodkor Stadium), built in 2012 and accommodating 34,000 spectators. This stadium is also a home for the [[FC Bunyodkor|Bunyodkor Football Club]].

